summary: An Ordinance accepting the quit-claim deed of Ewing M. Smithers, Fred G. Smithers and Ada Thorne to the City of Seattle as executed on the 16th day of July, 1906, to a strip of land sixty-six (66) feet in width extending northerly and southerly across a portion of Government lot five (5) of Section nineteen (19), township twenty-five (25) North, Range four (4) East, W. M.
